Your Honor,

I, Charlotte Porter, am here before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I accept full responsibility for my actions on the day in question, where I engaged in aggressive driving and exceeded the permitted speed limit while also using my phone.

I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members who were arriving. Unfortunately, due to my lateness, I made a poor decision to drive aggressively and answer a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. As a result of my reckless behavior, I crashed into a guardrail. I am grateful that no one else was harmed in this incident, and I understand the potential danger my actions posed to myself and others on the road.

I acknowledge that I already had 3 penalty points on my license for speeding, which highlights my lack of regard for traffic regulations on previous occasions. I deeply regret my thoughtless actions, and I now realize the immense consequences that could have arisen from them. It is clear to me that I must take full responsibility for the harm I have caused by my careless driving.

In terms of mitigation, I am 37 years old and have maintained a clean record up until this incident. I have consistently adhered to the law and actively contributed to my community through regular donations to the British Heart Foundation. I hope that this demonstrates my commitment to being a responsible and law-abiding citizen.

While I understand that my remorse cannot undo the damage caused, I assure the court that I am genuinely remorseful for my actions. I am fully aware of the potential dangers of reckless driving and the importance of adhering to traffic laws. I am committed to learning from this experience and taking steps to ensure that I never engage in such behavior again.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I acknowledge the gravity of my actions and the potential harm I could have caused. I respectfully request the court to consider my clean record, my contributions to society, and my genuine remorse when determining an appropriate sentence for this offense.

Thank you for your attention.

